<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🕷️ M003 Extension — Build the Spider (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Spider (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner (Extension, after Week 6) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>Build a red spider in 3D — <strong>red body</strong>, <strong>eight legs</strong>, <strong>two eyes</strong>. Every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>: x <strong>across</strong>, y <strong>up</strong>, z <strong>deeper</strong> (forward).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move, and the spider moves too.</p>
<p>🎨 Red parts = <strong>red concrete</strong>. Eyes = <strong>black wool</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the code. Circle one word.</p>
<pre><code>place red block at (1, 1, 2)
place red block at (1, 1, 3)
place red block at (1, 1, 4)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. This leg steps... Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<pre><code>place red block at (1, 1, 2)
place red block at (5, 1, 2)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only x changes. This jumps from the left side to the right side. Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>An eye sits <strong>up high on the front</strong> of the body, at (2, 3, 3). The code below has only <strong>two</strong> numbers, so it drops flat on the floor.</p>
<pre><code># broken
place black block at (2, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fill the blank to fix it:</strong></p>
<pre><code>place black block at (2, 3, __)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which number fills the blank? Circle one:</strong> 3 · 9</p>
<p><strong>What was missing? Circle one:</strong> the z number · the color</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Look at the 🕷️ spider in the world. Walk around it. See the fat body, the eight legs spread out, and the two eyes on the front.</p>
<p><strong>Build a small spider on your home spot.</strong> Keep it easy:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Red body: fill red blocks from (2, 2, 3) to (4, 3, 4) — a small block.</p>
<p>Four legs on the left: red block at (1, 1, 2), (1, 1, 3), (1, 1, 4), (1, 1, 5).</p>
<p>Four legs on the right: red block at (5, 1, 2), (5, 1, 3), (5, 1, 4), (5, 1, 5).</p>
<p>Two black eyes on the front: black block at (2, 3, 3) and (4, 3, 3).</p>
<p>💡 Tip: legs stay <strong>low</strong> (small y). Left legs all share x = 1, right legs all share x = 5. Each leg steps <strong>deeper</strong> (bigger z).</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera at the spider. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your <strong>one</strong> video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
